01:51.612 --> 01:53.214
And again, they're not pearls.

01:53.247 --> 01:55.683
They're just
white plastic beads.

01:55.716 --> 01:58.586
Yeah, well, now I have no
earrings to wear to the wedding.

01:58.619 --> 02:00.821
I've seen that dress.
You don't need earrings.

02:00.854 --> 02:03.491
You need a rim of salt
around your head.

02:03.524 --> 02:06.294
How's it going with Patrick?

02:06.327 --> 02:09.330
It's not. I've been stuck
in traffic for hours.

02:09.363 --> 02:11.665
I'm close to peeing
in my Big Gulp.

02:11.699 --> 02:14.802
If you do, make sure
you dump it out the window.

02:14.835 --> 02:16.637
I had a bad experience once.

02:19.273 --> 02:22.276
After all this, I just hope
he's home when I get there.

02:22.310 --> 02:23.911
You didn't call first?

02:23.944 --> 02:26.480
No! You don't call ahead

02:26.514 --> 02:28.816
when you're about to make
a big romantic gesture.

02:28.849 --> 02:31.352
Have you never seen
a Sandra Bullock movie?

02:31.385 --> 02:33.554
Not willingly, no.

02:33.587 --> 02:38.459
You don't call before you run to
the airport to stop the plane,

02:38.492 --> 02:40.461
or bang on the church window,

02:40.494 --> 02:44.598
or go back in time
to make sure your parents kiss.

02:44.632 --> 02:47.167
You just do it.

02:48.236 --> 02:50.638
Mom

02:50.671 --> 02:52.806
Damn it.

02:52.840 --> 02:55.209
If you're there,
I can't hear you.

02:55.243 --> 02:56.610
Mom?

02:56.644 --> 02:58.279
I'm pretending
I can't hear her.

02:58.312 --> 02:59.647
It drives her crazy.

03:01.014 --> 03:03.317
Mom?

03:03.351 --> 03:05.219
Mom!

03:05.253 --> 03:06.554
