then we can wait.

10:13.413 --> 10:15.182
No, I don't want to wait.

10:15.215 --> 10:16.917
I just want to look
back on tonight

10:16.950 --> 10:21.421
and be like,
"aw," not "meh."

10:21.454 --> 10:24.391
Well, nobody's looking
for "meh."

10:24.424 --> 10:27.160
It's just that if the
first time isn't great,

10:27.194 --> 10:29.396
then the next time you're
worried it won't be good again,

10:29.429 --> 10:31.164
and then you're all
messed up in your head,

10:31.198 --> 10:33.333
and then the
pressure's really on.

10:33.366 --> 10:37.204
I never thought of it
that way.

10:37.237 --> 10:39.673
But I am now.

10:41.141 --> 10:43.276
You know what?
I'm being ridiculous.

10:43.310 --> 10:44.878
Of course it's gonna
be perfect,

10:44.912 --> 10:46.113
because it's you and me.

10:46.146 --> 10:48.782
Yeah.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.751
You know what?

10:50.784 --> 10:52.352
Let's do it
right here, right now.

10:52.385 --> 10:54.387
Oh.

10:54.421 --> 10:57.257
Ha. Well, you're-you're-you're
putting a lot of pressure

10:57.290 --> 10:58.959
on the next six minutes.

10:58.992 --> 11:01.895
Let's take this party
to the back.

11:01.929 --> 11:03.363
