maybe we should.

15:54.387 --> 15:59.126
Oh, boy, I'm so glad
we didn't give up on this.

15:59.159 --> 16:00.327
Me, too.

16:00.360 --> 16:03.096
I mean, the-the
long-distance thing

16:03.130 --> 16:06.299
could have been a lot
for other people, you know?

16:06.333 --> 16:10.003
I mean, we could've just
started seeing someone else.

16:10.037 --> 16:13.173
I'm really happy we didn't.

16:15.442 --> 16:17.177
We didn't, right?

16:20.180 --> 16:22.215
Well...

16:23.450 --> 16:25.618
Why on Earth would
you tell Patrick

16:25.652 --> 16:27.320
you slept with
another guy

16:27.354 --> 16:29.656
right before you were about
to sleep with Patrick?

16:29.689 --> 16:31.191
It just came up.

16:31.224 --> 16:33.460
How?
I brought it up.

16:34.494 --> 16:36.596
Cold SpaghettiOs?

16:36.629 --> 16:38.298
That says self-loathing.

16:38.331 --> 16:42.469
Yeah, and I'm using the spoon
that snags your lip.

16:42.502 --> 16:45.172
Ow.

16:45.205 --> 16:47.174
I deserve that.

16:47.207 --> 16:48.675
So why did you tell him?

16:48.708 --> 16:51.811
I didn't want to start the
relationship off with a lie.

16:51.844 --> 16:55.148
That's fine, but you got to
bang their brains out first.

16:55.182 --> 16:57.450
Then you can be honest.

16:57.484 --> 16:59.186
I do it with Adam
all the time.

16:59.219 --> 17:00.320
It's the main
reason we have sex.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.589
Oh, it is not.

17:03.690 --> 17:05.692
You and Adam are great together.

17:05.725 --> 17:07.794
I'd give anything
for what you have.

17:07.827 --> 17:10.497
Not today. We had
a huge fight.

17:10.530 --> 17:13.233
All of a sudden he wants a
traditional church wedding.

17:13.266 --> 17:16.336
Doesn't he know that if you walk
into a church wearing white,

17:16.369 --> 17:18.405
you'll burst into flames?

17:19.406 --> 17:21.308
Thank you.

17:29.516 --> 17:32.585
Mom

17:32.619 --> 17:35.488
Are you somewhere in here
having sex?

17:37.190 --> 17:38.691
Boy, I hope not.

17:40.193 --> 17:42.095
Patrick.

17:43.596 --> 17:45.798
This is for me?

17:45.832 --> 17:48.568
Well, you're not the only one

17:48.601 --> 17:51.438
who can make
a big romantic gesture.

17:52.472 --> 17:55.642
* Slow ride

17:55.675 --> 17:56.743
* Take it easy...

17:56.776 --> 17:59.512
Sorry, uh, wrong song!

17:59.546 --> 18:01.381
I-I work out to that.

18:01.414 --> 18:02.549
Okay.

18:02.582 --> 18:03.783
That's supposed to be Seal.

18:03.816 --> 18:06.286
And, uh, oh, sorry.

18:06.319 --> 18:07.887
Oh, I-I-I can't find it.

18:07.920 --> 18:10.323
Uh, look,
j-just try to imagine

18:10.357 --> 18:12.625
"Kiss From a Rose"
playing in the back...

18:18.165 --> 18:20.133
I love that you
did all this.

18:20.167 --> 18:23.403
I'm-I'm so sorry
I overreacted.

18:23.436 --> 18:25.172
You easily could have lied
and I never

18:25.205 --> 18:26.273
would have known.
I forgive you.

18:26.306 --> 18:27.340
Bedroom's this way.

18:27.374 --> 18:28.608
Uh...

18:28.641 --> 18:31.244
Oh, damn it.
What?

18:31.278 --> 18:32.545
I forgot condoms.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.347
Oh, I got
a ton of 'em.

18:34.381 --> 18:35.715
Don't think about it.

18:35.748 --> 18:37.584
Just get up here.

18:51.931 --> 18:53.200
Hey.

18:53.233 --> 18:54.567
Thanks for coming over.

18:54.601 --> 18:56.603
I don't like the way
we left things the other day.

18:58.438 --> 19:00.440
:
Wow, Bonnie.

19:00.473 --> 19:02.342
You didn't have
to do all this.

19:02.375 --> 19:04.211
Oh, no, I...

19:04.244 --> 19:06.813
Yes, yes, I did.

19:06.846 --> 19:09.516
I absolutely did.

19:09.549 --> 19:12.619
Because I love you.

19:17.457 --> 19:20.327
I love you, too. Mmm.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.495
Look, I don't want to fight
about wedding stuff.

19:22.529 --> 19:24.697
I don't either. Let's just
kick the can down the road.

19:24.731 --> 19:26.233
Or, I've been thinking,
why don't we throw out

19:26.266 --> 19:27.534
the can altogether?

19:27.567 --> 19:29.202
What does that mean?

19:29.236 --> 19:30.770
Let's just keep things
the way they are

19:30.803 --> 19:32.705
and stay engaged forever.

19:32.739 --> 19:34.807
But I want to marry you.

19:36.843 --> 19:40.513
Well, I asked you six months ago
and you won't set a date.

19:40.547 --> 19:43.583
You know, clearly, you don't
want to be the big candle.

19:43.616 --> 19:45.718
I do. I do want to
be the big candle.

19:45.752 --> 19:47.820
Let's just be happy
with what we have.

19:51.724 --> 19:53.393
No.

19:53.426 --> 19:55.228
Next year.

19:55.262 --> 19:57.364
First weekend in June. Done.
Bonnie, Bonnie.

19:57.397 --> 19:58.498
We're doing it.
I just did it.
Bonnie, we don't...

19:58.531 --> 20:00.400
Deal with it.
Order the doves.

20:00.433 --> 20:01.701
Esp...
Watch this.

20:01.734 --> 20:03.336
I'm gonna put it
in the calendar.

20:04.704 --> 20:07.374
Adam Barnabus Janikowski,

20:07.407 --> 20:08.875
did I just get played?

20:08.908 --> 20:10.877
Still not my middle name.

20:10.910 --> 20:12.612
And that depends.

20:12.645 --> 20:14.247
Should I open this card

20:14.281 --> 20:15.748
that's sitting in "my" flowers?

20:17.484 --> 20:19.852
June it is.

